        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 4:31PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 431 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles west of Owen Lake, or 37 miles northwest of Faith, moving east
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Owen Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
northwestern South Dakota.</instruction>
